tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is impaired as indicated by elevated creatinine. Cholesterol is mildly elevated, which may increase cardiovascular risk. All other parameters, including glucose, electrolytes, liver enzymes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for renal function and consideration of lipid management as appropriate for age and comorbidities.
